15 7. Receive and act upon complaints from disciplinary action and
16 grievances filed by state employees employed to perform duties as
17 outlined in paragraph 6 of subsection E of Section 3311 of Title 70
18 and Section 2-105 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes and to
19 establish rules pursuant to the Administrative Procedures Act as may
20 be necessary to carry out this objective and the right to be heard.
21 C. Complaints shall be filed with the Civil Service Division
22 within ten (10) business days of the date of when such action
23 occurred and hearings shall take place within thirty (30) business
